<br>
The simple fact is that no matter how I presented my case to him it was simply refuted, the reasoning being that magician pets are simply overpowered and the only correction to balance needed is that they be hammered. On several occassions I pointed out that melee classes are experiencing the end of their own Magician-style Kunark / Velious era and that the cycle would surely swing around, that right now it was finally a Magician's time to shine.<br>
<br>
If someone with such a long game history and usually objective opinion can make such a claim, then there is cause for some concern.<br>
<br>
It also appears plain to me that some people simply object to magician pets out damaging <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>anyone</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, as though a pet as an entity must be below average joe Knight damage in order for the world to be right. &quot;It's just a pet after all&quot; is a very common sentiment to many. I was then asked to consider the possibility that mage nukes were the overpowered side of the equation.<br>
<br>
Why is it OK for a Rogue to do tremendous damage, often twice that of a mediocre Monk or a decent Knight, and not for Mages? Why must we constantly tread this line between having comparable nukes to Wizards, and not stepping on melle toes?<br>
<br>
Gosh, I feel like a hybrid now ... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=colleen2>Colleen2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 252<br> <font color=#333333>(11/7/02 11:49:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=394.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~interruptrequest/gir.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cry.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: It Begins</span><hr size=1> It's a bolt, for one, meaning it's fairly situational when it comes to raiding.  And the pet requires a back to do that much dps.<br>
