Hehe please don't try to down play the mages power to me of all people. I have not complained about mages in awhile. I am pissed about the mage epic but that is for another thread. The mage class is in good shape for the first time in a long time. Lets not try to down play that power in fear it will be nerfed. I think we are in very good shape, and I don't believe we will be nerfed. I think Verant realized that without Mod Rod2 there was no place for the mage in Norrath so they upped our damage to respected levels. The very reason that classes are screaming for mage nerfs show you that our power is starting to get respect. Every time I see a wizard emote a /sigh when I crit for 4600 I smile inside. It makes up for all the months of seeing wizards call mages there &quot;Rod Bitch&quot; daily on the Graffe. Surely you haven't forgotten I know I haven't.<br>
<br>
I remember when alot of the top end monks that I am friends with on my server told me to dump the mage because they are worthless. Now it is the mage that is riding high, and finally people are wishing they could do what we can do. I kinda like it personally. I love the fact that primal equiped monks drool over my new rogue pet that I am slowly falling in love with. I love the fact people are begging me to do trial groups because they want a mage for damage.<br>
<br>
Don't get me wrong I really have a hard time getting a group. People still don't know that mages are the damage kings, and they should be happy to get us when they can. With whiny bitchfess threads like over at Monkly Business the word that we rock will get out faster then parses of damage ever could.  I say it is good that other classes are jealous of us. When people are jealous it means you have something valuable that they want or don't have. Finally we can do something no one else can. Be happy and enjoy the moment because we all know it won't last. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
