<br>
And that's the point.  Instead of being a balanced offensive/defensive class, monks are now *purely* a damage class.  Monks, the same as magicians, have a *single* defensive capability now.<br>
<br>
Which puts monks in the position of directly competing with magicians for that final damage-dealer spot in a group.  If magicians are perceived to fill that position better, monks will lead the charge calling for nerfs, or at least join in force when the wizards do.<br>
<br>
At least before, monks could solo some if they couldn't find a group.  That's not really an option now.  And before, monks could fill in as a tank in a pinch (though clerics would still prefer a warrior).  That's *really* not an option now.<br>
<br>
If monks as a whole figure out that magician pets out *tank* them, there will be a huge amount of complaints and calls for a nerf.<br>
<br>
<br>
EDIT: Sony doesn't really know anyway.  Luclin and PoP AA skills include double riposte, kick-riposte and damage mitigation skills.  Those are skills that are useful for a tank and useless for someone standing behind the mob.<br>
