<br>
Prior to PoP, mages weren't really known as good damage dealers. With rods, we could churn it out especially with rune items and FT10..<br>
<br>
Prior to PoP, monks were kick ass damage dealers.<br>
<br>
Post PoP, people are starting to notice just how good our damage dealing is, especially with FoT. People are starting to want mages in groups (PoJ trials are a good sign of this).<br>
<br>
So in relative terms, mages have had massive improvements recently. But then when we sucked so badly before, it's not that big an &quot;actual&quot; increase. <br>
<br>
Monks on the other hand went from being supertanks to random-death machines. So it's natural that they're lashing out at those who they perceive to have had massive gains in power. It's not right (no class should want any other class to be nerfed), but I can understand it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=durash>Durash</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 191<br> <font color=#333333>(11/7/02 4:56:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=394.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cry.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: It Begins</span><hr size=1> Monks can go walk some rice paper.  They're still stinging from getting their defense nerf, and as far as I'm concerned, they're welcome to duel Gonad.  <br>
