<br>
First, I personally think magicians should be the #1 damage dealer.  I think they're pretty close if not already there.<br>
<br>
But...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>In a normal exp group, the pet will outdamage any melee if well positionned and well equiped.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Most of this is coming out now because some monk with a tranq staff parsed himself on luclin mobs and said &quot;Fuxor My dps is only 65&quot;.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
My DPS raid-buffed is ~120 DPS and I have many weapons upgrades available to me yet.  I haven't seen anyone claim magician pets put out 120 DPS.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   The addition of the nukes is what gets you the #1 spot, and is what keeps monks and even moreso rogues from screaming bloody murder.  We know your mana runs out and there are other limitations to nuking.<br>
<br>
My magician, level 60 with epic and shock boots, can beat that DPS, but can't keep beating it indefinitely.  Ahh yeah, I do play a magician (and probably did before most of yours existed <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ), and do have first-hand knowledge of their strengths and weaknesses in comparison to monks.<br>
<br>
Higher level magicians should be able to beat it steadily, but then I should be able to get weapon upgrades as well that keep me running close.<br>
<br>
As far as the fist nerf goes, it was largely irrelevant to monks.  All it was was an insult after the real nerf.  18/20 sounds nice until you realize what you have to give up to get that.  I would have to give up ~200 hp, ~30 AC, ~20 to all resists, ~50 ATK, ~10 to all stats, and 40 percent self haste when the enchanter has more important things to do or (gasp) there isn't an enchanter in the group.  All that for a minor damage upgrade that may very well not turn out to be an upgrade at all after considering what's been given up.  But at least it was an option worth considering and comparing.<br>
<br>
As it is, I'm wielding weapons two expansions old with the same 15/20 ratio as the 15/20 level 65 fists.  I can give up all that I mention above...  to be wielding fists with the same ratio.  There's no option to be considered there.<br>
<br>
As to this:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I see monks, namely monks with a good amount of ac, feelin zero affects from the nerf.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Monk defense will be altered such that they may continue wearing the same equipment, however, they will get a decreased benefit to their overall ability to take damage.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Swing the nerf bat hard, swing it wide, and *hope* you hit the target.  Sony has never had the greatest aim.<br>
<br>
I don't think magicians need nerfed.  I think they're just fine where they're at.  But then, I didn't think monks needed nerfed either, and they took the biggest single hit a class has ever taken (and of course the nerf entirely missed the monks that actually *could* tank as well as or better than warriors, go figure).  So my opinion means little.<br>
<br>
I do think you'll see people calling for a nerf to magicians soon.  I do think monks will either be leading the charge or following the wizards.<br>
